{"id":"ev_d3c182ac2f2e405b","runId":"run_219","type":"delegation","at":1782296546170,"data":{"workItemId":"wi_ccbac86760f24338","atom":0,"task":"Surface the latest wrap-disposition into Oz's founder-facing run surface (read/display only).\n\nContext: A prior priority shipped a recorded `wrap-disposition` event with values `archive-candidate` | `awaiting-founder` | `continue`, derived by `deriveWrapDisposition` in `packages/core/src/runner/runner.ts` and emitted into the run's event stream. The disposition is currently only legible through the wrap closeout text; it is NOT shown in Oz's run-list / DebStatus surface (`renderDebStatus` in `packages/core/src/runner/status.ts`). The founder cannot see a priority's true disposition — especially an `archive-candidate` — at a glance.\n\nWhat to change:\n1. First, discover the owners (do not trust this description as exhaustive): grep for `wrap-disposition` and `deriveWrapDisposition` across `packages/core/src/` to find (a) exactly how/where the event is recorded into the event stream and (b) the shape of the recorded payload. Read `renderDebStatus` in `packages/core/src/runner/status.ts` and whatever run/status model it consumes.\n2. Project the LATEST recorded `wrap-disposition` event for each run into the run-list / DebStatus surface so it renders next to the run. Read it from the recorded event — do NOT recompute or re-derive the disposition in the projection. `deriveWrapDisposition` in runner.ts remains the single owner of derivation; the projection only reads the already-recorded value.\n3. If no `wrap-disposition` event has been recorded for a run yet, render a neutral absence (e.g. omit it or show a blank/`—`) — do not invent a default disposition.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- The latest `wrap-disposition` value appears in the Oz run-list / DebStatus surface, derived by reading the recorded event (one owner; no recomputation in the projection).\n- A test pins the projection to the recorded event: given a run whose event stream contains a `wrap-disposition` event, `renderDebStatus` (or the projection helper) surfaces that exact recorded value; and a run with no such event renders the neutral absence.\n- `pnpm typecheck` (or the repo's typecheck) is clean and the existing status/runner test suites pass.\n\nWhat must NOT break:\n- Do not change `deriveWrapDisposition` or how the event is emitted — this is read/display only.\n- Do not recompute the disposition anywhere outside its existing owner.\n- Do not alter unrelated fields of `renderDebStatus` output; existing rendering tests must stay green.\n\nWrite-scope: `packages/core/src/runner/status.ts` and its colocated test(s); read-only elsewhere. Report the exact files changed, the test command you ran, and its output."}}
